{"amendments":[{"body":"`run_id` is still not enforced as a required start/completion identity. `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:97-123` and `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:401-495` still expose `run_id: Option<&str>`, while `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:473-541` and `src/adapters/fs.rs:2820-3331` still implement the old runless started-at fallback/backfill flow (`find_matching_running_task_run`, `matching_finalized_task_runs`, `unique_terminal_replay_match`). That means a bead can still be started without a run ID and later finalized by matching a runless row, which is exactly the ambiguity Issue 2 was supposed to remove. Make `run_id` required in the service/port APIs, keep `TaskRunEntry.run_id` optional only for serde compatibility, delete the runless matching/backfill branches, and remove or rewrite the legacy tests that still assert this behavior in `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:1030-1217` and `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:4673-4724,5691-5749`.","rationale":"The accepted amendment said run identity must be known before `record_bead_start`; the current implementation and tests still permit the deprecated runless path."},{"body":"`plan_hash` is still optional at bead start and the snapshot-derived backfill machinery is still active. `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:97-105` and `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:401-437` still allow `plan_hash: Option<&str>`, and `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:286-292` plus `src/adapters/fs.rs:2570-2624,3020-3027,3052-3071,3403-3415` retain `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation`, `snapshot_plan_hash`, and `safe_plan_hash_backfill`. That leaves lineage rows dependent on mutable snapshot state instead of the controller’s dispatch-time hash, which is the behavior Issue 3 explicitly asked to remove. Make `plan_hash` required in `record_bead_start`, drop the snapshot provenance/backfill fields and helpers, and rewrite the tests that currently codify the rejected contract in `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:4727-4819,5392-5962`.","rationale":"Keeping snapshot-based inference/backfill means plan identity is still reconstructed from later state rather than passed explicitly by the caller, so the complexity and failure modes from Issue 3 remain."}],"summary":"The tracked diff is only comment churn in `src/adapters/fs.rs`, but reviewing the milestone-lineage model/service/adapter code end-to-end shows that only Issue 1 is actually addressed. Issues 2 and 3 remain unimplemented: runless `run_id` handling and snapshot-driven `plan_hash` backfill are still present in the public APIs, adapter logic, and unit tests. Targeted tests `cargo test plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot` and `cargo test find_matching_running_task_run_backfills_named_replay_with_matching_started_at` both pass, confirming the deprecated behaviors are still expected by the suite."}